\series bold 

\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{k}$
\end_inset 


\series default 
.
 The state with particle numbers 
\begin_inset Formula $n_{s}$
\end_inset 

 in each mode with momentum 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{k}_{s}$
\end_inset 

 (where 
\begin_inset Formula $s=1,2,...$
\end_inset 

 is an index that enumerates the excited modes) is defined by
\begin_inset Formula \begin{equation}
\left|n_{1},\, n_{2},\,...\right\rangle =\left[\prod_{s}\frac{\left(\hat{a}_{\mathbf{k}_{s}}^{+}\right)^{n_{s}}}{\sqrt{n_{s}!}}\right]\left|0\right\rangle .\label{eq:exc state}\end{equation}

\end_inset 

We write 
\begin_inset Formula $\left|0\right\rangle $
\end_inset 

