status Collapsed

\layout Standard

\backslash 
startremark
\end_inset 


\series bold 
 Remark: choosing the cutoff function.

\series default 
 We regularize the series by the factor 
\begin_inset Formula $\exp(-n\alpha/L)$
\end_inset 

 and not by 
\begin_inset Formula $\exp(-n\alpha)$
\end_inset 

 or 
\begin_inset Formula $\exp(-nL\alpha)$
\end_inset 

.
 A motivation is that the physically significant quantity is 
\begin_inset Formula $\omega_{n}=\pi n/L$
\end_inset 

, therefore the cutoff factor should be a function of 
\begin_inset Formula $\omega_{n}$
\end_inset 

.
 Also, renormalization will fail if the regularization is chosen incorrectly.
 
