\end_inset 

.
 The frequency is approximately constant except for a finite time interval,
 for instance 
\begin_inset Formula $\omega\equiv\omega_{0}$
\end_inset 

 for 
\begin_inset Formula $t\leq t_{0}$
\end_inset 

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\omega\equiv\omega_{1}$
\end_inset 

 for 
\begin_inset Formula $t\geq t_{1}$
\end_inset 

.
 It is usually impossible to find an exact solution of Eq.\SpecialChar ~
(
\begin_inset LatexCommand \ref{eq:osc var omega}

\end_inset 

) in such cases (of course, an approximate solution can be found numerically).
 However, the solutions in the regimes 
\begin_inset Formula $t\leq t_{0}$
\end_inset 

