\end_inset 

As usual, we expect 
\begin_inset Formula $\langle\hat{N}_{\Omega}\rangle$
\end_inset 

 to be divergent since it is the total number of particles in the entire
 space.
 As discussed above, the divergent volume factor 
\begin_inset Formula $\delta(0)$
\end_inset 

 represents the volume of space, and the remaining factor is the density
 
\begin_inset Formula $n_{\Omega}$
\end_inset 

 of 
\begin_inset Formula $b$
\end_inset 

-particles with momentum 
\begin_inset Formula $\Omega$
\end_inset 

:
\begin_inset Formula \[
\int_{0}^{+\infty}d\omega\left|\beta_{\omega\Omega}\right|^{2}\equiv n_{\Omega}\delta(0).\]

\end_inset 

 Therefore, the mean density of particles in the mode with momentum 
\begin_inset Formula $\Omega$
\end_inset 

